adviseScripts.text: Commander, Mihara hasn't been spending as much time with me lately...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Is she sick of me or something?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Try throwing a hissy fit.
Use physical force to keep her with you.
I tried that already, but it didn't work...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh* Whatever should I do...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yes, that's it! It's time to get physical.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'll give Mihara a few good whacks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Yuni about Mihara.
I'm in a real pickle.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I want to buy some handcuffs and a whip,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: but I don't have enough money to get both!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Tie Mihara up with the whip.
I'll buy them for you.
Ah-ha!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Of course! How could I forget such a basic maneuver?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the advice, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I appreciate the offer, Commander...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But if you did that, then they wouldn't truly belong to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni lectures me about the uses of various instruments.
Capturing Raptures is my job, but I'm no good at it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Commander, do you know what happens to a Rapture once it's captured?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: They're studied and then returned to their home.
... They probably get disposed of.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text:
I'm not a child, you know.
You don't have to lie.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Nevertheless, thank you for being so considerate.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: ... That's what I thought.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Everyone else lies to me when I ask them that question.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But not you, Commander. You're a good person.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I have a light-hearted conversation with Yuni about the Raptures.
I want to use this whip to attack the Raptures,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: but Mihara always stops me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Why? I'm much better with a whip than a gun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Because Raptures don't feel any pain.
Because the whip hurts more than the gun.
Ah...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: That's why... I guess even if I did use it, they wouldn't be able to appreciate it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You're so smart, Commander!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: No, Commander. That's not it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: It's not a matter of which hurts more. It's something else entirely.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni teaches me how to use the whip.
Mihara says that when I'm sleeping, I try to grab anything I can get my hands on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Not that long ago, I broke something of Mihara's that she cherished.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything I can do to change my sleeping habits?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: What about tying up your hands before you go to sleep?
Find something to hold onto before you go to sleep.
Hmm... I'm not really into that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: It sounds uncomfortable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: That's genius!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: From now on, I'll find something that I can hold onto before I go to sleep.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Yuni about sleeping habits.
One day, if all the Raptures are gone,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: and the world is peaceful once again...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: what should I do? I certainly won't be able to capture Raptures anymore.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Just live out your days in peace.
How about running a club with Mihara?
Ha ha! Okay.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: That sounds nice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: After all, we'd be living in a world where nothing in particular needs to be done, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: That's a good idea, but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: If the world changes, then I want to change along with it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Yuni about the distant future.
Mihara really tore into me just now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I tied up the cookie bag so tightly that the cookies inside got crushed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But what's the point of tying a knot if you don't make it tight?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Even if it breaks, the cookies are still cookies. No harm no foul.
You should tie Mihara up, too.
No, Commander. Once it breaks, it is no longer the same.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: It can never return to what it was before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: ... Yes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Since Mihara punished me, I'll just have to punish her back.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni teaches me how to tie a knot.
Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: How would you feel if someone suddenly hit you, out of the blue?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: One-sided violence is never good.
I would want to retaliate.
Yes, I feel the same way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: There needs to be mutual consent when it comes to these things.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Speaking of, would you... consent to that kind of arrangement?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Ha ha! I see you're the type who doesn't like to lose.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But, surely there's a better option than just retaliation?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni and I explore the philosophy behind hitting others.
My precious handcuffs! They're broken...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I had them for so long...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Should I buy a new pair?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'll buy you an identical pair.
Is it really that big a deal that the handcuffs are broken?
Hm... No. It's okay.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: It wouldn't be the same.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'll just have to fix these ones.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You're right! It doesn't really matter if the handcuffs work or not.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: They're just a prop. The important thing is who you put them on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni tells me about her most treasured possessions.
Commander, what kind of hit hurts the most?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: A hit to the shins? A punch to the gut? Stubbing your toe?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I haven't been hit that much, so I really can't say.
It hurts no matter where you get hit.
Ha ha! You're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Then, would you let me teach you...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: No way. They can't all be the same.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Commander, you're either lying, or you really don't know anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But that's not a problem. Just let me teach you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni teaches me a lot of things.
Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: What would you say is my strong suit?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You're pure of heart, and kind.
You're adorable.
Hehe,
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Mihara said the same thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm glad that you feel the same way she does.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Being cute is not a strength.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: It seems you don't know me that well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni and I have a conversation about her strengths.
Commander, have you ever drank a cocktail before?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I really want to try one, but Mihara says I'm still too young.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: What does it taste like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: When you're a little older, we can go try a few together.
They taste... as if they have an air of danger to them. It's all very adult.
That'd be great.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Um...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Could Mihara come with us too?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: How intriguing...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm not sure how I'd handle it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I explain more about cocktails to Yuni.
Mihara...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: means the world to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm sure Mihara likes you as well.
She means the world to me too.
You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Mihara likes me too...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm happy to hear you say that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Wait...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You mean you like Mihara more than me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni and I talk about Mihara.
I'd prefer to be alone today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Caress her hair.
Take out a candy.
Thank you, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I feel much better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I am not in the mood for candy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm feeling down today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I try my best to make Yuni feel better.
Commander...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm not bothering you by talking to you every day, am I?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You've never bothered me, not even once.
Honestly, sometimes it's a bit too much.
Hehe, that's good.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I was worried you might find it irritating...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: So it's somewhat difficult for you to handle, is that it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But I like spending time with you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni and I have a nice heart-to-heart.
Commander, give me your hand.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I want to show you something fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You reach out your hand.
You reach out with your foot.
Yuni slaps your hand.
*Wazzzzzzuuuuup*
Hehe, isn't that great?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Commander, what are you doing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: That's not your hand... is it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni asked me again to reach out my hand, but I refused.
Commander, I don't want to go to orientation.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I pick things up by doing them, not hearing about them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Do I really have to go?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: It's important to read up on things you're learning as well.
Anything worth learning can be learned on the battlefield. You don't have to go.
... Mihara said the exact same thing...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Fine, I'll go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Really, I don't have to go?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But Mihara said I had to...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: If I skip orientation, Syuen will...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm so confused. I don't know what to do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni suddenly seemed downcast, so I consoled her.
Hmm... Mmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni was fiddling around with the whip.
Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Do you like me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yes, I do.
Before we talk... could you put the whip down?
That's a relief!
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I thought you didn't like me. It felt like you were avoiding me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I like you as well, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Say what?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: What about the whip?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm starting to think you care about this whip more than you do about me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I speak a little more with Yuni, attempting the entire time to convince her to drop the whip.
I'm so exhausted...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: You can go and sleep.
Do you want to sleep here?
I don't feel like leaving.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I want to sleep here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Is it okay?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, you're the best, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'll sleep here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Yuni fell asleep on the sofa.
Mihara says a hobby is something that makes you happy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Commander, when are you most happy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: When I'm spending time with you.
When I'm spending time with Mihara.
You enjoy spending time with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I'm happiest when I'm around you and Mihara.
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: But...
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: What about me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: Do you not enjoy spending time with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Yuni

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Yuni about what makes us happy.
